#: 231ea11823a84d8e91897dee2b85e553
msgid ""
"To launch a disposable template from the command line, execute the "
"following command in dom0:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-disposables.rst:107
#: ac8fe50b77894804b4a38310b1b5c8b5
msgid "Opening a file in a disposable via GUI"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-disposables.rst:110
#: cfa809f52a654de2b0c74ab4b70664c0
msgid ""
"In an app qube’s file manager, right click on the file you wish to open "
"in a disposable, then choose “View in disposable” or “Edit in "
"disposable”. Wait a few seconds and the default application for this file"
" type should appear displaying the file content. This app is running in "
"its own dedicated qube – a disposable created for the purpose of viewing "
"or editing this very file. Once you close the viewing application the "
"whole disposable will be destroyed. If you have edited the file and saved"
" the changes, the changed file will be saved back to the original app "
"qube, overwriting the original."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-disposables.rst:112
#: 17e43456f8ab4c0f9ce9d7a1bc5b1431
msgid "r4.0-open-in-dispvm-1.png"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-disposables.rst:117
#: d5af44f5f26143d3ab1ccb478b097dc9
msgid "r4.0-open-in-dispvm-2.png"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-disposables.rst:123
#: dcfbd2093f14484bbda6b4e4b767e935
msgid "Opening a fresh web browser instance in a new disposable"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-disposables.rst:126
#: 2256ab5fc7ff47e3936b6ead12d63777
msgid ""
"Sometimes it is desirable to open an instance of Firefox within a new "
"fresh disposable. This can be done easily using the app menu: just go to "
":menuselection:`Application Menu --> Disposable --> Disposable: Firefox "
"web browser`. Wait a few seconds until a web browser starts. Once you "
"close the viewing application the whole disposable will be destroyed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-disposables.rst:128
#: b3cf87c164a744eab8ecfaa9819f4995
msgid "r4.0-open-in-dispvm-3.png"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-disposables.rst:134
#: 4becf6bda8aa4decb633ff3c27a83104
msgid "Opening a file in a disposable via command line (from app qube)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-disposables.rst:137
#: 5c4a20ea912b4161af0ea740fc29c354
msgid "Use the ``qvm-open-in-dvm`` command from a terminal in your app qube:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-disposables.rst:145
#: 237cbb0d0baa425a9ccdff22319e4c36
msgid ""
"Note that the ``qvm-open-in-dvm`` process will not exit until you close "
"the application in the disposable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-disposables.rst:148
#: d482725d94b3488695a0c8c99650eb6b
msgid "Making a particular application open everything in a disposable"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-disposables.rst:151
#: 62ed3a6dd54b4616a53d28ecea84333b
msgid ""
"You can use the ``qvm-service`` command or the services GUI to cause an "
"application in a qube to open files and URLs in a disposable. To do this,"
" enable a service named ``app-dispvm.X`` in that qube, where ``X`` is the"
" application ID. For instance, to have Thunderbird open all attachments "
"in a disposable, enable the ``app-dispvm.thunderbird`` service."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-disposables.rst:153
#: a29494e261d04b6a8c75992ebc6833e7
msgid ""
"This feature is currently somewhat experimental, and only works for Linux"
" qubes. It is known to work with Thunderbird and Wire, but it may fail to"
" work with some applications that do not honor all XDG environment "
"variables. If the feature does not work for you, please file a bug "
"report."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-disposables.rst:156
#: c59ec3d0df284cb89f595609e29fc214
msgid "Opening particular types of files in a disposable"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-disposables.rst:159
#: 8c38cb7d079e4f6881e4a2955827e51b
msgid ""
"You can set ``qvm-open-in-dvm.desktop`` as the handler for a given MIME "
"type. This will cause all files of that type to open in a disposable. "
"This works in disposable templates too, but be careful: if your "
"disposable template is set to use ``qvm-open-in-dvm.desktop`` to open a "
"certain kind of file, every disposable based on it will be as well. If "
"the disposable template is its own default disposable template (as is "
"often the case), this will result in a loop: ``qvm-open-in-dvm`` will "
"execute ``qubes.OpenURL`` in a new disposable, but that will in turn "
"execute ``qvm-open-in-dvm``. The cycle will repeat until no new "
"disposables can be created, most likely because your system has run out "
"of memory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-disposables.rst:161
#: a665b62ae44c47cb88251e8cba6fdb7c
msgid ""
"This will *not* override the internal handling of PDF documents in Web "
"browsers. This is typically okay, though: in-browser PDF viewers have a "
"fairly good security record, especially when compared to non-browser PDF "
"viewers. In particular, the attack surface of PDF viewing in Firefox is "
"usually less than that of viewing an ordinary Web page."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-disposables.rst:164
